[I think of a virus of "alarming proportions" as one about 2.54 cm in
diameter, otherwise I guess they mean the numbers of cases has reached
alarming proportions. Although this newspaper report suggests that Ross
River virus "has reached alarming proportions in NSW", it also indicates
that public awareness may have led to the increases in numbers of reported
cases. What is needed are apparent:inapparent infection rates. If Richard
Russell would care to comment on this report we would appreciate it. -
